Package com.intellij.xdebugger.frame

Class XValueMarkerProvider<V extends XValue,M>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.xdebugger.frame.XValueMarkerProvider<V,M>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    JavaValueMarker

    public abstract class XValueMarkerProvider<V extends XValue,M>
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides implementation of 'Mark Object' feature.

    If debugger values have unique ids just return these ids from getMarker(XValue) method. Alternatively implement markValue(XValue) to store a value in some registry and implement unmarkValue(XValue, Object) to remote it from the registry. In such a case the getMarker(XValue) method can return null if the value isn't marked.

      • getMarker

        public abstract M getMarker(V value)
        This method is used to determine whether the value was marked or not. The returned object is compared using Object.equals(Object) method with markers returned by markValue(XValue) methods.

        This method may return null if the value wasn't marked by markValue(XValue) method.

        Returns:
        a marker for value
